  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p>The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date of this permission.</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\nREASON: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).</p><p>\r\n</p>",
    "<p>Detailed drawings/full particulars of the proposed development showing the matters set out below must be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority, in writing, before any work is commenced. The development shall not be carried out otherwise than in accordance with the details thus approved which shall be implemented in full.</p><p>\r\na) Type of insulation proposed, the build up and the interface with window reveals and at the eaves.</p><p>\r\nREASON: To comply with&nbsp;LP1 Design Quality and Local Character</p>",
    "<p>The Development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans hereby approved and any subsequent approval of details.\r\n</p><p><br></p><p>\r\nREASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved.\r\n</p>",
    "Prior to commencement of works, and retrofit statement including full details of the design of the proposed insulation (and any other related systems including fixings, support and services) and replacement doors and windows must be submitted and approved by the Local Authority. The report must include:&amp;nbsp;A comparison of the existing and the proposed thermal performances (u value) and g-values for both EWI and replacement doors &amp;amp; windowsA comparison of the existing and the proposed EPC ratingsSpecifications of all materials and products used in the proposed EWI system and replacement doors and windows, including their specific thermal performance per component and as a system (u value) and g-values for windowsDetail drawings (maximum scale 1:20) of the proposed build-up of the EWI (section drawing, elevation drawing, detail of key junctions/interfaces including with the roof/eaves/ground) with commentary on thermal bridging mitigation where applicablePrior to the occupation of the development, a Final “as-built” retrofit statement shall be submitted and approved by the Local Planning Authority confirming the following key metrics have been achieved or improved upon the pre commencement figures :As-built U-values using &#x27;through wall&#x27; calculations for each component and relevant datasheetsFinal EPC certificateREASON: In the interest of addressing climate change and supporting net zero development in accordance with LP55 of the Hackney Local Plan and Section 14 of the National Planning Policy Framework."
  ],
